## Description
Add support for parsing and registering the `permission` field from agent markdown frontmatter so that beads-planner-agent can have the question tool enabled via frontmatter configuration.

## Root Cause
The agent loading system doesn't support permissions:
1. `AgentDef` type doesn't have a `permission` field
2. `loadAgents()` doesn't parse `permission` from frontmatter
3. `KnowledgeBaseService` doesn't copy `permission` when registering agents

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1: Update AgentDef type
File: `src/kb/types.ts` (around line 18)

```typescript
export interface AgentDef {
  name: string;
  description?: string;
  prompt: string;
  mode?: "subagent" | "primary" | "all";
  model?: string;
  permission?: Record<string, any>;  // Add this line
}
```

### Step 2: Parse permission from frontmatter
File: `src/kb/loaders/agents.ts` (around line 89, after mode parsing)

```typescript
      if (frontmatter["mode"]) {
        const mode = frontmatter["mode"] as "subagent" | "primary" | "all";
        if (["subagent", "primary", "all"].includes(mode)) {
          agent["mode"] = mode;
        }
      }

      // Add permission parsing
      if (frontmatter["permission"]) {
        agent["permission"] = frontmatter["permission"] as Record<string, any>;
      }

      agents.push(agent);
```

### Step 3: Copy permission when registering agents  
File: `src/service/knowledge-base-service.ts` (around line 255)

```typescript
        config.agent[agent.name] = {
          prompt: renderedPrompt,
          ...(agent.description && { description: agent.description }),
          ...(agent.mode && { mode: agent.mode }),
          ...(agent.model && { model: agent.model }),
          ...(agent.permission && { permission: agent.permission }),  // Add this line
        };
```

### Step 4: Add debug logging
File: `src/service/knowledge-base-service.ts` (around line 261)

```typescript
        this.logger.debug(`Registered agent: @${agent.name}`, {
          hasPermission: !!agent.permission,
          permission: agent.permission,
        });
```

## Files to Modify
- src/kb/types.ts (AgentDef interface)
- src/kb/loaders/agents.ts (loadAgents function)
- src/service/knowledge-base-service.ts (agent registration)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] AgentDef includes optional permission field
- [ ] loadAgents parses permission from frontmatter
- [ ] KnowledgeBaseService copies permission to config
- [ ] Debug logging shows permission being registered
- [ ] TypeScript compiles without errors
- [ ] beads-planner-agent.md frontmatter permissions are applied

## Notes
This makes plugin agents work the same way as config-defined agents - permissions in frontmatter are properly parsed and applied.
